Package: EcoZonal
Title: Hotspot Detection and Distributional Comparisons for Ecosystem Service Change
Version: 0.0.1
Authors@R: 
    person("Jeronimo", "Rodriguez-Escobar", , "jeronimo.rescobar@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: ESZonalR provides downstream analytics for ecosystem service change: it ingests zonal statistics computed upstream (e.g., via a Python pipeline), computes land-cover change metrics for polygons (R/exactextractr), identifies per-service hotspots under flexible threshold rules, produces mapping-ready outputs, and generates effect-size–centered comparisons of hotspot vs non-hotspot distributions (KS D, AUC, Cliff’s δ with BH adjustment), alongside density overlays, ECDF grids, and heatmaps. 
